- Frontend: Streamlit 1.x, Plotly 6.x
- Reporting: FPDF2 2.8.7

6.2 Key Implementation Details

6.2.1 Mean Imputation (Preprocessing)
Files Modified: train_model.py, predictor.py, app.py
```python
# Step 1: Load data
df = pd.read_csv('data/heartt_cleveland_cleaned.csv')

# Step 2: Separate features and target
X = df.drop('target', axis=1)
y = df['target']

# Step 3: Apply mean imputation
imputer = SimpleImputer(strategy='mean')
X_imputed = pd.DataFrame(
    imputer.fit_transform(X), 
    columns=X.columns
)

# Step 4: Save imputer for prediction
joblib.dump(imputer, 'models/imputer.pkl')
```

6.2.2 Model Persistence
```python
# Save all required objects
joblib.dump(best_model, 'models/model.pkl')
joblib.dump(scaler, 'models/scaler.pkl')
joblib.dump(imputer, 'models/imputer.pkl')  # NEW
joblib.dump(X.columns.tolist(), 'models/feature_names.pkl')
```

